Answer:
"Under the CCPA, businesses that collect the personal information of California residents must comply if they meet any of the following criteria: 

Have gross annual revenues in excess of $25 million; 
Buy, receive, or sell the personal information of 50,000 or more California residents, households, or devices; 
Derive 50% or more of their annual revenues from selling California residents' personal information. 
Reference: Cal. Civ. Code § 1798.140(c)(1)"
